##  Do’s :-

- Think before posting anything online  
- Keep your account privacy settings secure  
- Use respectful and polite language while commenting  
- Share positive and useful content  
- Report fake accounts or inappropriate content  
- Use social media for learning and networking  
- Verify information before sharing it  

##  Don’ts :-

- Do not share your passwords with anyone  
- Do not accept friend requests from strangers  
- Do not post abusive or negative comments  
- Do not click suspicious links  
- Do not share OTP or personal information  
- Do not spread fake news  
- Do not post everything about your personal life  

##  Personal Note

As a student, I believe social media should be used carefully because it creates our digital identity. Using it responsibly can help us in learning and building our future, while careless use can create problems.
